Boil a large #pot of salted @water{to cover} for the @dried linguine{180%grams}.

When the water is boiling, add the linguine then bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the #pot. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Clean and roughly chop the @mushrooms{250%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%unit} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place a large #pan over medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, fry the @chorizo{100%grams} until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of @oil{to taste} (if necessary) to the #pan with the mushrooms and garlic. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Fry until browned, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add the pasta, @green pesto{1%sachet} and @creme fraiche{125%grams}.

Stir well and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide your creamy pesto and chorizo pasta between #bowls. Garnish with the @grated Italian style hard cheese{50%grams}.